    Inspecting a CSV-W

    This page is designed to help you inspect an existing CSV-W.

    A transcribed video walkthrough

    Pre-requisites

    You should have already installed csvcubed, designed your CSV input and built your CSV-W.

    Inspecting your CSV-W cube

    To inspect the sweden-at-eurovision-no-missing.csv-metadata.json data cube we built in Building a CSV-W, we run the csvcubed inspect command:

    1
    csvcubed inspect sweden-at-eurovision-no-missing.csv-metadata.json

    All being well we get the below output. A detailed explanation of this output is provided in csvcubed inspect section.

    1

    Errors

    There are a number of errors that can occur when inspecting a CSV-W; most of them are designed to help ensure you get correct and valid outputs.

    Please see our documentation explaining a number of common errors to see what you can do to diagnose and correct any errors which occur.

    Next

    This is the end of the quick start section, however there is a lot more information available in the guides section; see the left-hand menu.

    The next logic action to take with the Sweden at Eurovision data set is to learn how to describe missing data so we can include contestants who weren't able to perform.
